prompt: Create a comparative outcomes infographic for open versus endovascular treatment of mesenteric ischemia. LAYOUT: Side-by-side comparison with OPEN SURGERY on the LEFT half and ENDOVASCULAR on the RIGHT half, separated by a central dividing line. TOP SECTION - ACUTE MESENTERIC ISCHEMIA: Two columns with matching data visualization. MORTALITY: Open showing bar at "40-70%" (red-orange gradient), Endovascular showing bar at "25-50%" (blue gradient) with asterisk "Selected series, significant selection bias". TECHNICAL SUCCESS: Open bar at "85-95%" (green), Endovascular bar at "70-90%" (green-yellow). BOWEL ASSESSMENT: Open shows checkmark "Direct visualization", Endovascular shows X "Requires separate procedure". MIDDLE SECTION - CHRONIC MESENTERIC ISCHEMIA: 3-YEAR PATENCY: Open bar at "80-90%" (excellent/green), Endovascular bar at "50-70% primary / 80-90% assisted" (two-tone bar). PERIOPERATIVE MORTALITY: Open bar at "5-10%" (yellow-orange), Endovascular bar at "2-5%" (green). REINTERVENTION AT 5 YEARS: Open bar at "10-15%" (green), Endovascular bar at "30-40%" (yellow-orange). BOTTOM SECTION - KEY CONSIDERATIONS: Two icon panels. Open surgery panel: Icons for "Direct bowel assessment", "Durable repair", "Higher upfront risk", "Longer recovery". Endovascular panel: Icons for "Less invasive", "Faster recovery", "May require reintervention", "Cannot assess bowel". CENTER BOTTOM: Arrow pointing down to "INDIVIDUALIZED DECISION BASED ON: Peritonitis status, Anatomic suitability, Patient risk factors, Bowel viability certainty". VISUAL STYLE: Clean data visualization, infographic style with horizontal bar charts, consistent color coding (green=better, yellow=moderate, red=worse), professional medical presentation quality. White background, modern sans-serif typography placeholder areas.
